DATED MATERIAL, SUBJECT TO CHANGE. PLEASE CONSULT CURRENT UCSD GENERAL CATALOG FOR ANY ADDITIONAL INFORMATION.


Effective Fall 2022, major preparation will be required for this major. For details, visit: http://admissions.ucsd.edu/MajorPrep


Special Advising Note:


Transfer students must complete the following preparatory courses for their major before enrolling at UC San Diego: One lower division economics course (Econ 1 OR Econ 3); principles of accounting (MGT 45) OR both Financial Accounting (MGT 4/Econ 4) and Managerial Accounting (MGT 5); as well as two required math classes (Math 10A and 10B, OR Math 20A and 20B).  Students are strongly advised to complete the third required math class, (Math 10C or 20C) before enrolling at UC San Diego. Students are not able to begin their upper division core economics courses 

until Math 10C or 20C is complete. Please review the major requirements checklist and suggested 2 year plan on this webpage: https://economics.ucsd.edu/undergraduate-program/major-minor-requirements/BusEcon.html


The Business Economics major will train students to operate within firms and to understand how firms operate within markets. Training in core economics disciplines (microeconomics, macroeconomics, econometrics) will teach students how firms interact with markets, how economies function, and how to extract insights from data. Training in core business disciplines (accounting, finance, management, marketing, operations, strategy) will teach students how to perform various functions inside businesses. Electives will deepen students' skillsets after core training is complete.


With an understanding of economic fundamentals and functions of businesses, students will graduate with the knowledge required for their first day on the job as well as the skills needed to predict and respond effectively to future changes in their industry, the workplace and the world.


When choosing which mathematics series to take, Math 10A-B-C or Math 20A-B-C, it is important to remember that only Math 20A-B-C allows students access to UC San Diego’s upper division math courses that are recommended as preparation for Ph.D. study in economics and business administration, as well as for graduate studies for professional management degrees, including the MBA. Therefore, while we require economics majors to take Math 10A-B-C, we strongly recommend that economics students take Math 20A-B-C.


For more information please visit https://economics.ucsd.edu/undergraduate-program/index.html
